Package com.sicomsa.dmt.solicitude

Interface Solicitude

All Superinterfaces:
DownloadRegistry
All Known Implementing Classes:
BatchSolicitude, DefaultSolicitude
public interface Solicitude extends DownloadRegistry
Represents a download request to the massive download web service, with its status and information that is collected as the steps are invoked to download the digital certificates.

A Solicitude initially contains the client making the request and the query options and filters. As it executes the web services, it gathers information. For example, the query identifier and the instant it was accepted through the "request download service". Later it gathers the download information through the "verify request service", and so on.

Since:
1.0
Version:
2024.11.09
Author:
Beto Lopez

    • pause

      void pause()
      Pauses this Solicitude.

      To make a download, you need to follow certain steps: request, verify, download one package, then the next one, etc. Pausing a request means not continuing with the next process until a download is requested again.

      See Also:
      • DefaultSolicitude.download(jakarta.xml.soap.SOAPConnection)

    • getReject

      SatResponse getReject()
      Returns the SatResponse indicating that the request was not accepted by the web service and therefore caused this Solicitude to be rejected.

      This response can be casted to SolicitaResponse, VerificaResponse, or DescargaResponse depending on which service generated the response.

      Returns:
      the SatResponse indicating that the request was not accepted by the web service and therefore caused this Solicitude to be rejected.
